# Privacy Policy — Day & Night Journal

_Last updated: June 27, 2026_

Day & Night Journal ("the app," "we," "us") is built to be private by design. This
policy explains exactly what the app does and does not do with your information.

## The short version

We do not have a server. We never receive, see, store, sell, share, mine, or use your
journal to train anything. Your data lives on your device and in **your own private
iCloud account** — nowhere else.

## Information the app uses

**Your journal entries.** Everything you type or select — prompts, notes, checklists,
moods, water counts, and any custom fields you create — is stored locally on your
device using Apple's on-device database, and synced across your own Apple devices
through your private iCloud (CloudKit) account. We have no access to this iCloud
container; only you do, through your Apple ID.

**Apple Health data (optional, read-only).** If you choose to enable it, the app reads
your sleep times, step count, and exercise minutes from Apple Health to automatically
fill in the matching journal fields. This access is **read-only** — the app never
writes to Apple Health. These values become entries in your own private journal and are
synced only through your private iCloud, exactly like anything else you enter. They are
never sent to us or any third party, and are **never used for advertising, marketing, or
data mining**. You can turn Health off at any time in the iOS Settings app, and you can
decline it entirely; the app works fully without it.

**Sign in with Apple.** The app uses Sign in with Apple solely to gate access to your
journal. We store only the anonymous, stable user identifier that Apple provides, on
your device. We do not collect your name or email, we operate no account server, and we
store no authentication tokens anywhere off your device.

**Notifications.** The app schedules a local weekly reminder on your device. These are
local notifications only — no push server is involved and no information leaves your
device to deliver them.

## What we do NOT collect

- No analytics, tracking, advertising identifiers, or third-party SDKs.
- No usage telemetry sent to us.
- No location data.
- Nothing transmitted to any server operated by us — because we operate none.

## Data sharing

We do not share your information with anyone, because we never have it. Your data syncs
only through Apple's iCloud under your own Apple ID, governed by
[Apple's Privacy Policy](https://www.apple.com/legal/privacy/).

## Deleting your data

You are always in control:

- **Sign out** (in the app's About screen) returns you to the sign-in screen while
  leaving your journal safe in your iCloud.
- **Delete account & all data** (in the app's About screen) permanently erases every
  entry and custom field from your device and your iCloud. This cannot be undone.
- You can also delete the app and remove its iCloud data via iOS Settings → your name →
  iCloud → Manage Account Storage.

## Children

The app is not directed at children and collects no personal information for any user.

